My topic is describe famous place you once visited.  When I was freshman in a university, I visited Kyoung-ju with my girlfriend. Kyoung-ju has many historical land mark.  The first, Kyoung-ju, was the capital city of Sin-la during the period of the three states.  Many king's tombs are located in Kyoung-ju. So, if you go there, usually you will see the king's tombs.
Second, Kyoung-ju has the most famous budhist temple, Bul-guk-sa. UNESCO adobted this temple as world tresure. UNESCO stand for the United Nations Educational Scientific and Sultural Organization. So, if you go there, you can see traditional Korean pictures and many beautiful places. In conclusion, if you want to learn about Korean traditional culture, I recommand that you visit Kyoung-ju.

I will compare Pittsburgh and my home town, Busan. First of all, the population of Busan is one million more than the population of Pittsburgh. Second, Pittsburgh's weather and Busan's weather are not parallel. The climate of Busan is usually stable. On the other hands, Pittsburgh's weather is terribly diverse in every seasons. Lastly, Busan has many festivals. Also, it has many sightseeing places. This is because Busan is located in the south of South Korea where is bordered by the Pacific Ocean. However, Pittsburgh has many universities which are high class universities in the world. Also, it has many historical and art museum. In my opinion, Busan is more close to sightseeing city and Pittsburgh is more close to educational city. From my perspective, if someone want to travel, I will recommand Busan more than Pittsburgh but if someone want to study, I will recommand Pittsburgh more than Busan.
